{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:02:03.276060+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I have all the information needed. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## How to Start This FastAPI Template with Docker\n\n### Prerequisites\n- Docker and Docker Compose installed.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Create a `.env` file** by copying the provided example:\n   ```bash\n   cp .example.env .env\n   ```\n\n2. **Edit `.env`** and set the values described below (especially `SECRET_KEY` and the Postgres credentials).\n\n3. **Launch all services** (FastAPI app, PostgreSQL, Redis):\n   ```bash\n   docker-compose up --build\n   ```\n   This spins up three containers:\n   | Service | Image | Exposed Port |\n   |---|---|---|\n   | `web` | Built from the repo's `Dockerfile` (Python 3.9) | `11000` |\n   | `postgres` | Official `postgres` | `5432` |\n   | `redis` | `redis:alpine` | `6379` |\n\n   The `web` service runs `python main.py`, which starts **uvicorn** on the host/port defined by your `.env`.\n\n4. The API will be available at `http://localhost:11000/api/v1/`.\n\n---\n\n### Environment Variables You Must Prepare\n\nAll values are read by `app/settings.py` from the environment. The file `.example.env` is the template. Here is every variable and its purpose:\n\n| Variable | Purpose | Example Value | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `ALLOWED_HOST` | Uvicorn bind address | `0.0.0.0` | OK to keep as-is for local Docker use |\n| **`SECRET_KEY`** | **JWT signing key** (used with `HS256` / `passlib` bcrypt) | `meandyouaretogether` | **Change this to a strong random secret** |\n| `DEBUG` | Toggle debug mode (`True`/`False`) | `True` | Set to `False` for production |\n| `PORT` | Uvicorn listen port | `11000` | Must match the `ports` mapping in `docker-compose.yml` |\n| **`POSTGRES_USER`** | PostgreSQL username | `sasori` | **Change for non-local environments** |\n| **`POSTGRES_PASSWORD`** | PostgreSQL password | `sasori` | **Change for non-local environments** |\n| `POSTGRES_DB` | Main application database | `akatsuki` | Created automatically by the Postgres image |\n| `POSTGRES_TEST_DB` | Test database | `hebi` | Used by the `TEST_DB_URL` in settings |\n| `POSTGRES_PORT` | PostgreSQL port | `5432` | Default is fine inside Docker |\n| `POSTGRES_HOST` | PostgreSQL hostname | `postgres` | Must match the Compose service name |\n| `REDIS_HOST` | Redis hostname | `redis` | Must match the Compose service name |\n| `REDIS_PORT` | Redis port | `6379` | Default is fine |\n\n**Minimum you should change before running:** `SECRET_KEY`, `POSTGRES_USER`, and `POSTGRES_PASSWORD` (the example values are insecure placeholders).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1124, "prompt_tokens": 10930, "total_tokens": 12054, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 427, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 10176}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "a17bdfd101b94fc8b73b6aaa5ea02dea", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead55-1e55-7ee2-9973-f07462a50765-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10930, "output_tokens": 1124, "total_tokens": 12054, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 10176}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 427}}}}]}}}
